&lt;p&gt;Join the Janus Fellows and the Sarah Doyle Women&#039;s Center for a free Faculty Club discussion on women&#039;s rights in the context of the &quot;war on women&quot; with Sara Matthiesen, a PhD candidate in the American Studies department. Sara is writing a dissertation about reproductive rights, how they get defined, and the social movements around them.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Do the recent controversies around women&#039;s reproductive rights constitute a &quot;war on women?&quot; How can we understand the issues beneath this &quot;war&quot;? What is at stake? Sara will give a brief introduction and will then lead discussion.&lt;/p&gt;
